<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-07T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="86" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2927: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">U. S. S. “George Washington,”</hi>
                                </placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-07T17:00:00-05:00">December
                                    7, 1918—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 8—12:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4. Your 2, December 5, 12 noon. For <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">Colonel
                                House</persName>. President suggests that arrangements for meeting
                            of Inter-Allied Conference be postponed until preliminary informal
                            discussions have shown just what would be best in all the
                            circumstances.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>